A '''Ribbon''' is a decoration on a character’s gravestone, awarded based on how they lived. Many different factors affect which ribbon a character receives when they die.

Currently, there are 40 different ribbons. The “Ribbons” tab in the Main Menu has a list of all 40, though ones which have not yet been earned are shown in grey. Four of the ribbons are secret – before a player earns them, the list shows question marks instead of a name and emoji.

The original 11 ribbons were: ''Academic'', ''Fertile'', ''Hero'', ''Lazy'', ''Loaded'', ''Lustful'', ''Mediocre'', ''Rich'', ''Scandalous'', ''Unlucky'', and ''Wasteful''. In April 2020, more were added including: ''Tarzan'', ''Gold Digger'', ''Monopoly'', ''Movie Buff'', ''Barbie Girl'', ''Veteran'', and ''Influencer'', as well as the first two secret ribbons.

__TOC__

== Regular Ribbons ==
These ribbons always appear in the ribbons list (when not owned), unlike the Secret Ribbons.

=== Academic ===
''[[File:Screenshot 20190531-114300.png|thumb|The "Academic" ribbon.]]''
''Complete a postgraduate education''

Difficulty: Easy

It is a yellow ribbon represented with a brain emoji.

Procedures to get the ''Academic'' ribbon:
* Focus on [[Education|school]] as much as possible by studying harder every year.
* Once your character reaches age 6, read your books and at age 12, go to the library each year to enhance your smarts.
* Attend university and keep on studying harder.
* Go to Graduate School or seek other higher education such as Medical School after your character graduates.
* Get a job that requires graduate school (e.g. teacher, lawyer, psychiatrist, nurse, veterinarian, etc.).

''[[File:Screenshot_20190808-164943_01.jpg|thumb|left|The "Addict" ribbon.]]''
=== Addict ===
''Die with addictions''

Difficulty: Extreme

It is a light pink ribbon represented with a pill emoji.

Procedures to get the ''Addict'' ribbon:
* Go to the horse racetrack and the casino often. Make sure your lifetime winnings from gambling are less than 1 million or else you will end up with the ''Highroller'' ribbon.
* Do NOT take drugs when offered, or else you might die from an overdose and get the "Stupid" ribbon.
*  If you have an addiction, '''never''' go to rehab.
*  You must die with at least two addictions to get this ribbon.

'''Notes: Becoming addicted to substances is a random chance, but getting so is important to get the badge. Avoid going to parties or clubbing too many times, or you will get the "Rowdy" ribbon instead. If you go clubbing less than 10 times in your life, you will not get "Rowdy".'''

=== Barbie Girl ===
''[[File:Barbie Girl ribbon.PNG|thumb|The "Barbie Girl" ribbon.]]''
''Go under many knives''

Difficulty: Easy

It is a pink ribbon represented with a doll emoji. You have to be born as a female or become a transgender female to get this ribbon. 

Procedures to get the ''Barbie Girl'' ribbon:
* Choose a low-profile, yet decent-paying career to afford many plastic surgeries. Do not become an actor, singer or any career in that industry to avoid the "Academic", "Famous", "Influencer", "Rich" or "Loaded" ribbons.
* Get every plastic surgery with the obvious exception of Gender Reassignment because you need to be born and die as a female, because if you do, you'll end up triggering another ribbon as a male.
* Also you can be born as male and get Gender Reassignment surgery, then get every plastic surgery procedures as a transgender female to get this ribbon.

'''Notes: If your character had a botched plastic surgery, you will never get the ribbon (unless it was Botox of Face Lift); even worse, if the damage is too high which can result in death, you will also never get the ribbon.'''

[[File:Screenshot_20190808-165018_01.jpg|thumb|left|''The "Cat Lady" ribbon.'']]
=== Cat Lady ===
''Be a spinster, surrounded by felines''

Difficulty: Varies

It is a creme ribbon represented with a kitty emoji. You have to be born as a female or transgender female to get this ribbon. 

Procedures to get the ''Cat Lady'' ribbon:
* Focus on adopting as many cats as possible and only spend time with your feline friends. You must own at least 30 cats throughout your life, and less than 5 pets of any other species.

'''Notes: You can have a maximum of three cats at a time if you are a non-[[Bitizenship|Bitizen]] or do not have a house.'''

=== Cunning ===
[[File:Screenshot_2019-08-22-22-37-12-74.png|thumb|''The "Cunning" ribbon.'']]
''Practice extreme Machiavellianism''

Difficulty: Medium

It is a blue and pink striped ribbon represented by theater masks. 

Procedures to get the ''Cunning'' ribbon:
* Commit a [[crime]] and get sent to jail.
* Escape jail by doing a hard maze puzzle.
* Get gender reassignment surgery.
* Emigrate to another country (optional). This will help you avoid getting caught, but you still need to get gender reassignment surgery to get the medal.

'''Notes: You may need to repeat the procedures above as you may get the "Mediocre" or "Wasteful" ribbon instead. It is also possible to get "Cunning" by committing few murders in one year and never getting caught, usually if the character dies under five years after one was committed, as it would lessen the chance of getting another ribbon.'''

[[File:Screenshot 20190530-205412.png|thumb|left|''The "Deadly" ribbon.'']]
=== Deadly ===
''Be responsible for the deaths of others''

Difficulty: Hard

It is a purple and black striped ribbon represented with a knife emoji.

Procedures to get the ''Deadly'' ribbon:
* Murder a lot of people! The minimum is five people to get this ribbon.
* Manslaughter also counts as murder even though it technically isn't. To do it, attack someone, using a martial art move or a powerful one like Uppercut to attack their weaknesses like jaw or throat, and the character may end up dying from their injuries. This is highly unreliable, though.
* If you get sent to jail but haven't killed enough people, you can escape by doing the maze puzzle<ref>Many videos and websites show solutions to escape certain mazes.</ref>. Its difficulties may vary through time, so it is best to attempt an escape once per year.
* If murder seems too risky, you can hire hitmen to kill the number of people required to score the ribbon. Keep in mind, the hitmen must kill them and not scam you. You need bitizenship to hire hitmen.

'''Notes: The easiest way to commit multiple murders is to join a crime syndicate, then commit the Extortion crime. When a victim refuses to give you money, you have the option to "whack them out." This usually has a high success rate, and you can simply refresh the game if the player is caught by the police. The most effective way to commit a murder without joining a crime syndicate is performing Drive-Bys, which just requires a driving license, but it can still fail, and if it does, the character may die. Another method would be to get a black belt in Taekwondo to learn the Double Roundhouse Kick, then attack someone with it to the skull (the option to attack in the skull isn't always present). Doing this has a pretty high chance of killing someone.'''

=== Family Guy ===
[[File:1E1EBB7F-8427-4058-8A95-C36FAF7C3652.jpeg11|thumb|''The "Family Guy" ribbon.'']]
''Be an honest, loving father''

Difficulty: Varies

It is a bright orange ribbon represented with an emoji of a father with kids. You have to be born as a male or become a transgender male to get this ribbon.

Procedures to get the ''Family Guy'' ribbon:

* Have a family (A wife and at least two children).
* Only have one spouse throughout your life.
* Spend time with your children every year for at least 30 years. Keep your karma high by complimenting and giving money to family members.
* Do not go to prison at any point.
* Do not abandon any children or pets.
* Do not have too many children to avoid "Fertile".
* Use the "Spend Time With All" button a few times a year. Requires the player to watch an ad if they are not a Bitizen.

[[File:Image.png|thumb|left|''The "Famous" ribbon.'']]
=== Famous ===
''Achieve fame in life''

Difficulty: Hard

It is a gold ribbon with stars as a pattern represented with a camera emoji.

Procedures to get the ''Famous'' ribbon:
* Get a job like a actor, singer, etc...
* Try to keep working harder and get promoted. Once you get a job as a lead actor, you will soon become a '''Movie Star!'''
* Keep your looks high by going to the gym and taking manicures. If your looks are lower than 80%, it is recommended to get low-cost plastic surgery like Botox to keep your looks high.
*There have since been more fame-worthy careers such as a singer, model, chef, writer, DJ, mobile app developer, politician, reporter and magician.
* Since the [[Royalty]] update, one can also be famous just by staying in royalty. This requires the player to be lucky enough to be born as one, marry into someone in royalty, or to use [[God Mode]] to be born into royalty.

=== Fertile ===
[[File:Screenshot_2019-01-30_at_1.21.30_PM.png|thumb|''The "Fertile" ribbon.'']]
''Spawn a lot of off-spring''

Difficulty: Medium

It is a green ribbon represented with a baby bottle emoji.

Procedures to get the ''Fertile'' ribbon:
* Have a lot of children through adoption, pregnancy of a partner or yourself, and possibly sperm donation. Your number of children multiplied by two plus your number of grandchildren must add up to at least 15, for example, you could achieve this through having 2 children and 11 grandchildren, or 5 children and 5 grandchildren. Having 8 children guarantees you will meet the requirements even if none of them have any grandchildren. Having/fathering 10 biological children in one lifetime gets the "Fabulously Fertile" achievement.

[[File:Generous ribbon.PNG|thumb|left|''The "Generous" ribbon.'']]
=== Generous ===
''Gift well and often''

Difficulty: Medium

It is a yellow ribbon with hearts represented with a wrapped gift emoji.

Procedures to get the ''Generous'' ribbon:
* Gift family, friends, and other relationships every year at least 30 items.
* Have much appreciated when gift them.
* Avoid arguments and if you get into one, either apologize or agree to disagree.

=== Geriatric ===
[[File:Ribbon_earner.jpg|thumb|''The "Geriatric" ribbon.'']]
''Live for a very long time''

Difficulty: Medium

It is a silver ribbon represented with an infinity emoji. You have to be the age of 120 or higher.

Procedures to get the ''Geriatric'' ribbon: 
* If your character has any illnesses, go see the doctor and cure them immediately.
* Keep your health and your happiness high to live longer, such as by heading to the gym and/or meditating. If you are sad, '''go on vacation''!
* Going on a good diet like South Beach or Mediterranean will also help.

'''Notes: Make sure you have 100% happiness every time before pressing "age" when your character is 100 or older. If your character is at 90-99% happiness, meditate, go to the movie theater, or compliment your family members until you are at 100% again. Having and maintaining high health is also important but does not need to be 100% like happiness does.'''

[[File:Bitlife2.jpeg|thumb|left|''The "Globetrotter" ribbon.'']]
=== Globetrotter ===
''Travel or emigrate to many countries''

Difficulty: Medium

It is a white ribbon represented with an Earth emoji. This ribbon sounds like exactly what it is. You will have to emigrate, have a honeymoon at or take a vacation to at least 20 countries to earn this ribbon.

'''Notes: Achieving this ribbon will need your character to have a high net worth, but do not make too much money or else you will get the "Rich" ribbon. '''

=== Gold Digger ===
[[File:Gold Digger ribbon.PNG|thumb|''The "Gold Digger" ribbon.'']]
''Get rich by marrying rich''

Difficulty: Hard

It is a dark green striped ribbon represented with a pickaxe emoji.

Procedures to get the ''Gold Digger'' ribbon:
* Having a high looks and stats and born in a wealthiest countries (such as Australia or Germany) is recommended to do this.
* You must never have a job.
* Use Freelance Gigs to earn quick money for use of Dating app and the wedding plan. Also you can steal items such as burglary or shoplifting to earn money as quick but not as many to avoid getting the ''Thief'' ribbon.
* Open Dating app to find the partners at older age with highest money income (green bar) and start dating them. Gift "BitLife Bitizenship" to them and propose instantly.
* Use God Mode to edit the partner with 0% willpower (optional).
* Propose and marry them at least 1 time or more. Plan your wedding at low-cost price (e.g Barn or Drive-Thru Wedding Chapel).
* You'll get money inheritance at least over $1.5 million through divorce or widow to earn this ribbon.

Notes: Even if you manage to propose to them and plan the wedding, having a crazy lover may backfire, as there is a high chance they will make you sign a prenup. This is especially counterproductive because if you agree to sign a prenup, you will not get the money through the divorce nor earn the ribbon.

[[File:Screenshot 2019-01-30 at 1.30.09 PM.png|thumb|left|''The "Hero" ribbon.'']]
=== Hero ===
''Save a life or die nobly''

Difficulty: Easy

It is a white ribbon represented with a superhero emoji. Another chance ribbon.

Procedures to get the ''Hero'' ribbon:
* If you attempt to [[Situation/SOS|save someone]] (By intervention, not by police or fire department), you will get you this ribbon. If you die saving someone, you will still achieve it. Successfully doing the Heimlich maneuver on a choking relative can also get this ribbon. Unlike the SOS situations, there is no risk that your character can face and they will not die trying to save them.
** Another way to achieve this ribbon if your character is deployed in the military is to fail the deployment minefield puzzle. To ensure you get the ribbon, fail on purpose and make sure it kills you. '''Failing the challenge but surviving the explosion will not count.'''

=== Houdini ===
[[File:Houdini.jpg|thumb|''The "Houdini" ribbon.'']]
''Escape from prison many times''

Difficulty: Extreme

It is a purple and navy ribbon represented with an unlocked lock emoji.

Procedures to get the ''Houdini'' ribbon:
* Go to jail and '''successfully''' escape, and then do it again, repeat this as many times as you can. The way to escape is the maze puzzle. This ribbon has been made significantly harder to earn since the August 2019 prison update.
* Escape at least 10 times to get this ribbon.
* Do not spend too much time in jail to avoid getting the Jailbird ribbon.
* Escaping Juvenile Prison also counts.

'''Notes: Although you can enlist in the military or emigrate illegally, this can still be a risky move as there is a high chance that you will end up in a maximum security prison and, unless you are familiar with the layouts, this can make it much harder to earn this ribbon and run the risk of getting the Jailbird ribbon instead.'''

[[File:Bitlife4.jpg|thumb|left|''The "Highroller" ribbon.'']]
=== Highroller ===
''Earn a lot of money gambling''

Difficulty: Luck-based

It is a dark green ribbon represented with a dice emoji.

Procedures to get the ''Highroller'' ribbon:
* Have a high net worth early on first.
* Go gambling by heading to either the casino or the racetrack. Gambling is illegal in some countries, so if your character is born in one of those, they will have to emigrate.
* Always bet the highest amount possible and try to win over a million dollar.
* Make sure your lifetime winnings from gambling stay at 1 million or higher. If you lose more money gambling after winning a million, you may not get the ribbon. Sometimes it will get the ''Addict'' ribbon instead.
*If you cannot win a million, at least try to have substantially more wins than losses and never bet the lowest amount of money.
** As of October 18, 2019 the iOS glitch for saving money by closing and reopening the app while gambling has been patched, making it harder for iOS users. This has not yet been patched on Android.

'''Notes: The casino is recommended because Blackjack is relatively simple to play and win. The racetrack is pure luck, but at the casino, you can at least somewhat influence the outcome.'''

=== Influencer ===
[[File: Influencer ribbon.PNG|thumb|''The "Influencer" ribbon.'']]
''Enjoy the life of a social media star''

It is a sky blue ribbon with verified check emoji.

Difficulty: Hard (Easier since the ''Social Media'' update)

Procedures to get the ''Influencer'' ribbon:
* Have a high health, looks and smarts. Sign up for social media accounts (Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, YouTube, TikTok, Twitch and OnlyFans) when you become 13 years old. (Note that you have to be 18 years old to be able to have an OnlyFans account.)
* Post a lot as many times as you can on social media often every year.
* Pick your correct posts, such as "Blog", "Challenge", "Dance", "Gaming", "Haul", "How-to", "Selfie", "Sexy Pic", "Skit", "Story", "Thirst Trap", etc. This helps you get more likes and followers.
* Get more million likes and a thousands of followers and try to go viral!
* Buy followers to increase them (optional, but not always recommended).
* Promote your products to increase your chances of followers.
* Monetize your account on YouTube if you have over 1k subscribers.
* If you have over a hundred-thousands of followers, get verified on social media accounts, then you'll become the '''social media star!'''
* Get verified on all social media accounts and have a million followers.
* Another easy way to get this ribbon is you can be a fame-related career life such as actor,  singer, writer or politician, verify on all social media accounts then do the procedures.

'''Notes: Trolling people too much will suspend your account for abusive behavior. Don't buy your followers too much because you'll get your account suspended for spamming purposes.'''

[[File:Screenshot 2019-07-09 at 3.45.00 PM.png|thumb|left|''The "Jailbird" ribbon.'']]
=== Jailbird ===
''Experience several stints in prison''

Difficulty: Easy

It is a black-and-white striped ribbon represented with a police car emoji.

Procedures to get the ''Jailbird'' ribbon:
* Go to jail, escape or get released, then commit another crime and be sent back. Serving two sentences or more will get you the ribbon. To get this ribbon may be easier if your character escapes more than once but not so much as to get the ''Houdini'' ribbon. However they must escape and go back at least once to avoid getting the "Cunning" ribbon.

'''Notes: Dying in prison during your second sentence may help you get the ribbon faster but is not required. As of the Prison Update, the ribbon is somewhat harder to achieve.'''.

=== Lazy ===
[[File:Screenshot_2019-01-30_at_1.12.20_PM.png|thumb|''The "Lazy" ribbon.'']]
''Live an idle life''

Difficulty: Extremely Easy

It is a blue ribbon represented with a sleeping face emoji. Another easy ribbon to receive.  Simply keep clicking the Age button and keep aging up. Don't get a job, don't go to the doctor, don't date, don't help - don't do a thing. '''Be lazy.''' Live to at least 50 years old without ever getting a job or joining the military. You must not get a job, even if a friend or family member tells you to do so. Your smarts must be higher than 10% or else you will get the "Stupid" ribbon. 

Notes: Even if you do contribute to some events in your life, make sure you never have a job and you may earn the Lazy ribbon.

[[File:Screenshot_20190808-165116_01.jpg|thumb|left|''The "Loaded" ribbon.'']]
